        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2124928175" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10725889933757297544">This book was recommended to be by a friend and at the time I just kind of passed it off but I kept coming across the name Clive Barker not realizing that he is such a huge horror Icon.<br/>I had a bit of a hard time tracking it down but when I finally found it and started it, it grossed me out right from the first page. <br/>That&apos;s a huge plus for me as I find a lot of horror novels very blah and I will catch myself skimming some paragraphs.<br/>I couldn&apos;t get enough of these stories.<br/>Barker took these words a</span>
  <span id="freeText10725889933757297544" style="display:none">This book was recommended to be by a friend and at the time I just kind of passed it off but I kept coming across the name Clive Barker not realizing that he is such a huge horror Icon.<br />I had a bit of a hard time tracking it down but when I finally found it and started it, it grossed me out right from the first page. <br />That's a huge plus for me as I find a lot of horror novels very blah and I will catch myself skimming some paragraphs.<br />I couldn't get enough of these stories.<br />Barker took these words and combined them in such a way that made me constantly cringe and on several occasions gag :D<br />The descriptions were perfect, perfectly real. </span>
